I haven't written in a looong time, I reckon I'm not much for words. The first week of school sucked, I hate all my classes, and I spent the better half of the last 2 days at work.  I got some maintenance on my car done this morning, my cousin Timmy helped me with it, and I'm glad he saved me about $400.  After that I went to home depot, and got Daniel to mix me some paint, then got Woofie to ring it up.  I finally got around to washing my car this afternoon, after trying to do so for nearly a week.  I need to get busy painting my room and studying for my quizzes on Monday and Tuesday.  Man it sucks to be back.  The show last night was great, even though I didn't stay long for Futch's band.  Sorry I couldn't make it out after the show, plans were just so spontaneous and up in the air I didn't know what was going on. Well i guess thats it. Wait....

Yeah that's it.

Maleficent in dusky rose
Gathered satin lapped Her breasts
Like blood upon the snow
A tourniquet of Topaz
Glistened at Her throat
Awakening, pulled from the tomb
Her spirit freed eclipsed the moon
That She outshone as a fallen star
A regal ornament from a far flung nebular

Her likeness hung in the black gallery
Commanding unease
Demanding of Death to breathe...

Midst the whirl and daylight fauna
Of society at court
Elizabeth bedazzled, Her presence sought applause
Though Her torchlit shadow
Thrown upon damp cellar walls
Greeted nothing but despair from slaves Her nights enthralled

Thirteen Winter solstices had shown
Her path, that the dark
Had marked its dominion
Spaying the confessor
Whose caresses she'd known,
As whipcord in the House of Dog
Her cold cunt meat on holy bone

Raped of faith, She now embraced
The narcissistic unrest frozen on the mirror's face
With this disdain, inside these veins
(Highborn wanton that She was)
She sought to keep what age would claim
Her soul was sold and for this toll
Reeking pyres ever smouldered
On the whims of one so in control
Elizabeth, mysterious.
Cruelty brought thee orchids
From the bowels of the abyss

Once upon atrocity when midwitches stifled cries
And carved abortive runes in reddened wombs
Exhumed by scrying eyes
Madness came upon
Her like an amourous lover's seed
Lifesblood splashed upon Her skin
In gouts torture unleashed

And to Her dead reflection
Twas as if Her pallor gleamed
Like an angel's warmed by candles
Where erotic stains had cleaved
So demons dragged this libertine

Upon the flesh of maidens preened
As canvas for caprice

Exacting obeisance
Her gaze held a seance
Of spirits too trapped under glass to commune
A sleeter mistress than Luna
Whose threats to consume Her
Met with torments giving vent to Her swoon

Flat on Her back
Pack-prey for the reams
Of verses and curses
That haunted Her dreams
Midnightmare chimed
Thirteen in Her mind
A disciple of scars
Branded years hissed behind
Ridden split-thighed
By the Father of lies
An ovation of wolves
Blushed the skies as they writhed

But Heaven is never forever

Today I was sitting in my Economics class, and the teacher told us the test was going to be next Monday.  Then some girl raised her hand and complained that we shouldn't have a test on a Monday after fall break because it isn't fair to the students because they will be having fun on their fall break and won't have time to study.  Now to most people this would sound like a fantastic idea, but I already have a test on Wednesday, so now I have two, because some stupid girl didn't want her weekend affected with having to learn.  I didn't think the teacher would do anything it except look at her like she was the dumbest person in the universe, but no, because one person didn't want to have their weekend spoiled by school, he gave in and changed the test date. 

Meanwhile, Joe Nathan finally brought his lunch today.  It only took 3 weeks but he did, and it was fun.  Everyone should bring their lunch to school, it is the COOLEST!
